The paper discusses the use of recurrent neural networks for forecasting intermittent demand, which is a problem commonly addressed in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also makes connections between renewal processes and current models used for intermittent demand forecasting, which falls under the category of statistics (cs.ST). Additionally, the paper presents empirical findings on intermittent demand data, which could be relevant to the sub-categories of social and information sciences (cs.SI) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
